trans-unit.source: #markup: Specifies that the array provides HTML markup directly. Unless the markup is very simple, such as an explanation in a paragraph tag, it is normally preferable to use #theme or #type instead, so that the theme can customize the markup. Note that the value is passed through \Drupal\Component\Utility\Xss::filterAdmin(), which strips known XSS vectors while allowing a permissive list of HTML tags that are not XSS vectors. (I.e, <script> and <style> are not allowed.) See \Drupal\Component\Utility\Xss::$adminTags for the list of tags that will be allowed.
